  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for an initial 20 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1607950853411-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1607950853411-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1607950853411-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1607950853411-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1607950853411-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chips are cooking, peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a pot over a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further – these are your <strong>caramelised onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1607951221054-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1607951221054-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1607951221054-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1607951221054-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1607951221054-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the<strong> rosemary leaves </strong>from their stems, then chop them roughly and discard the stems (hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves)</p><p>Slice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> slices</p><p>Combine the <strong>chilli relish </strong>and <strong>mayo </strong>in a small bowl – this is your<strong> chilli mayo</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>brioche buns</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1607951226829-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1607951226829-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1607951226829-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1607951226829-x1000.jpg",
